class Solution {
    public int findKthNumber(int n, int k) {
        long cur = 1;
        k--;
        while (k > 0) {
            long step = 0, first = cur, last = cur + 1;
            while (first <= n) {
                step += Math.min(n + 1, last) - first;
                first *= 10;
                last *= 10;
            }
            if (k >= step) {
                k -= step;
                cur++;
            } else {
                k--;
                cur *= 10;
            }
        }
        return (int) cur;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(n) + log(k))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a trie-like approach to traverse numbers in lexicographical order, efficiently calculating the number of nodes (step) between the current number and the next number at the same level, and decides whether to move to the next number or go deeper based on k and step.
